name: National Congress
description: Neoclassical building of the Argentine parliament; includes tours of its chamber and Eva Peron's Pink Room.

name: Obelisk
description: Emblematic white stone monument from Cordoba, inaugurated in 1936; it is a popular meeting point.

name: Colon Theater
description: This 1908 theater is famous for its acoustics; classical music concerts, opera, and ballet performances are held here.

name: Pink House
description: Venerable pink palace that is the seat of national executive power; guided tours are offered.

name: Tortoni Cafe
description: Iconic French-style cafe opened in 1858 and favorite place of the cultural elite with live tango.
